Class ParamRewardStruct

  • java.lang.Object
    • param.ParamRewardStruct

  • final class ParamRewardStruct
extends java.lang.Object
    Reward structure for parametric model. We only consider rewards assigned to a certain nondeterministic choice, because for the properties we consider, state rewards can be stored as equivalent choice rewards.
    Author:
    Ernst Moritz Hahn (University of Oxford)

      • instantiate

        ParamRewardStruct instantiate(Point point)
        Instantiate reward structure at a given point. That is, a reward structure is computed in which the corresponding values have been inserted for each parameter, and which is thus nonparametric.
        Parameters:
        point - instantiate for these parameter values
        Returns:
        non-parametric reward structure instantiated at given point

      • hasNegativeRewards

        public boolean hasNegativeRewards()
                           throws PrismException
        Returns true if there are negative rewards.
        Can only be called on a reward structure that has been instantiated, i.e., where all rewards are constant rational numbers.
        If either +/-Inf or NaN are encountered, an exception is thrown.
        Throws:
        PrismException
